This is how Sir Walter Jackson Cooper (1888 - 1973) is described in the Australian Dictionary of Biography. He was obviously a champion of returned soldiers which is most likely why this photo was taken outside Greenslopes hospital.

&quot;Tall and slender, he was modest, unassuming and unfailingly courteous to all, qualities which earned him the sobriquet of cabinet's 'first gentleman'.&quot;

Read the rest of his entry on the <a href="http://www.adb.online.anu.edu.au/biogs/A130549b.htm">Australian Dictionary of Biography</a> if you want to find out more about him. It is hard to imagine any modern political figure so flatteringly described.
